TopicTitle: KSPBlender - Blender Addon for importing .craft files (now with complete mod support!)

Articles.Content:
Hi, Im creating a model in blender but when I export it to .mu, this message appears and only the colliders and the nodes are saved.

![unknown.png](https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/710533770763173908/783089641733488690/unknown.png)
This is pretty much dead since it hasn't been updated in years and likely never will receive support for newer KSP versions and Blender versions.

> 
> 
> 3 hours ago, Delta dart said:
> 
> 
> This is pretty much dead since it hasn't been updated in years and likely never will receive support for newer KSP versions and Blender versions.
> 

Well, Taniwha's Blender .mu Import/Export Addon not only works for models, it can also do .craft file import. I'm not sure if it can export them after modification, or whatever, but might be worth looking into. Also, the thread title hasnt been updated, but it \*IS\* updated/working with Blender 2.83/2.9+ ... He has been doing regular updates for quite awhile now.
